# KeeLoq manufacturer key file — EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE
#
# This file documents the format used by the M1 firmware to look up KeeLoq
# manufacturer (master) keys for counter-mode re-encryption replay.
#
# ============================================================================
# HOW TO GET THE REAL KEYS
# ============================================================================
#
# The actual manufacturer keys are proprietary and cannot be distributed
# publicly.  You must extract them from your own Flipper Zero device:
#
#   1. Install RocketGod's SubGHz Toolkit on your Flipper Zero:
#        https://github.com/RocketGod-git/RocketGods-SubGHz-Toolkit
#
#   2. On the Flipper, run the toolkit and choose:
#        "Decrypt KeeLoq Manufacturer Codes"
#      This exports a file called keeloq_keys.txt to the Flipper's SD card.
#
#   3. Copy keeloq_keys.txt from your Flipper to your PC.
#
#   4. Encrypt for the M1 using the bundled script (RECOMMENDED):
#        python3 scripts/encrypt_keeloq_keys.py keeloq_keys.txt keeloq_mfcodes.enc
#
#   5. Copy the resulting keeloq_mfcodes.enc file to your M1 SD card at:
#        SUBGHZ/keeloq_mfcodes.enc
#
#   The firmware decrypts the file automatically — the plaintext never
#   needs to be on the SD card.
#
# ============================================================================
# ALTERNATIVE: PLAINTEXT FALLBACK (auto-migrated)
# ============================================================================
#
# If you already have a plaintext keeloq_mfcodes file on the SD card, the
# firmware will load it, automatically create the encrypted keeloq_mfcodes.enc,
# and delete the plaintext on the next boot.  No manual migration is needed.
#
# You can also create the plaintext file manually (see format below) and let
# the firmware migrate it.  Or use the older convert script:
#
#   python3 scripts/convert_keeloq_keys.py keeloq_keys.txt keeloq_mfcodes
#   # then copy keeloq_mfcodes (no extension) to SUBGHZ/ on the SD card
#
# ============================================================================
# FILE FORMAT (plain-text fallback / inside the encrypted payload)
# ============================================================================
#
# One entry per line.  Lines beginning with '#' are comments and are ignored.
# Blank lines are also ignored.
#
# Each entry has three colon-separated fields:
#
#   KEY_HEX:TYPE:MANUFACTURER_NAME
#
#   KEY_HEX          — 64-bit master key, exactly 16 uppercase hex digits
#   TYPE             — Learning type: 1 = Simple, 2 = Normal, 3 = Secure
#   MANUFACTURER_NAME — Free-form name (matched case-insensitively against
#                       the Manufacture: field in .sub files)
#
# Example entries (keys are illustrative placeholders — NOT real keys):
#
#   0123456789ABCDEF:1:ExampleCorp
#   FEDCBA9876543210:2:AnotherBrand
#   AABBCCDDEEFF0011:3:ThirdManufacturer
#
# ============================================================================
# ROCKETGOD FORMAT ALSO ACCEPTED
# ============================================================================
#
# The M1 firmware (and both scripts) also accept the RocketGod multi-line
# format directly.  Both formats may be mixed in the same file:
#
#   Manufacturer: ExampleCorp
#   Key (Hex):    0123456789ABCDEF
#   Key (Dec):    81985529216486895
#   Type:         1
#   ------------------------------------
#
# ============================================================================
# QUICK-START SUMMARY
# ============================================================================
#
#  Recommended (encrypted):
#    python3 scripts/encrypt_keeloq_keys.py keeloq_keys.txt keeloq_mfcodes.enc
#    → copy keeloq_mfcodes.enc to SUBGHZ/keeloq_mfcodes.enc on the SD card
#
#  Legacy (plaintext, auto-migrated on boot):
#    python3 scripts/convert_keeloq_keys.py keeloq_keys.txt keeloq_mfcodes
#    → copy keeloq_mfcodes to SUBGHZ/keeloq_mfcodes on the SD card
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Add your real entries below this line (delete or keep examples as desired):
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 0123456789ABCDEF:1:ExampleCorp
# FEDCBA9876543210:2:AnotherBrand
